{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":172338,"duration_api_ms":171474,"num_turns":28,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7f79c1cb-ded6-4891-83ee-a9adce1433e4","total_cost_usd":1.1072322499999996,"usage":{"input_tokens":22,"cache_creation_input_tokens":64243,"cache_read_input_tokens":1086907,"output_tokens":6486,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":64243,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":22,"outputTokens":6486,"cacheReadInputTokens":1086907,"cacheCreationInputTokens":64243,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.1072322499999996,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"The `StartJournalDetails` struct in `src/adapters/fs.rs` (line 2280) duplicates the field set of `StartJournalDetailsPayload` in `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs` (line 354). If a new field is added to the model's rendering function without updating the fs adapter's parsing struct, `StartJournalDetails::merge` will silently discard the unrecognized field during repair. Consider either: (a) making the model's `StartJournalDetailsPayload` public and adding `Deserialize` so fs.rs can reuse it, or (b) adding a compile-time or test assertion that the two structs stay in sync. The same issue already exists for `CompletionJournalDetails` — both pairs should be addressed together.","rationale":"Silent field loss during journal repair is a latent correctness bug. Today the structs are identical, but the two are defined in different files with no coupling, so drift is likely as the model evolves."},{"body":"In `FsMilestoneJournalStore::repairable_start_event` (fs.rs line 2482), if `existing.details` is `None`, the `?` operator causes the entire function to return `None`, which means the repair is silently skipped and a new (duplicate) event is appended. For `BeadStarted` events produced by this code, `details` is always `Some`, so this cannot happen today. However, adding an explicit guard or debug assertion (`debug_assert!(existing.details.is_some())`) would make the invariant self-documenting and catch regressions where a start event is somehow written without details.","rationale":"A `None` details field on a BeadStarted event would indicate a logic error elsewhere, but the current code silently degrades to appending a duplicate journal row instead of flagging the inconsistency."}],"summary":"The changes are correct, well-tested (113 tests pass), and implement the bead-to-task run linkage as specified. The `record_bead_start` journal event now uses structured JSON details (`render_start_journal_details`) instead of the old `project=...` plain-text format, the `repairable_start_event` repair path correctly handles idempotent retry and conflicting-run-id separation, and the new test covers the key scenarios (start journal dedup, same-timestamp named attempts kept separate, concurrent retries). No bugs or safety issues found. Two minor maintainability concerns raised: (1) duplicate struct definitions for journal details across model.rs and fs.rs that can drift silently, and (2) a silent `None`-details degradation path in `repairable_start_event` that should be explicitly guarded."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"d6efb9f8-2e7b-4517-bd18-7378aae8e925"}
